```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return lowercase(strip(col)) * "_" * replace(col, [" ", "-"] => "_")
end
```

This function first lowercases the column name using `lowercase()`, then strips any leading or trailing whitespaces with `strip()`. Finally, it replaces spaces and hyphens with underscores using `replace()`. The result is a string that has been cleaned according to the given instructions.
